				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yeah, when it's a toggle option, i think anything goes - it's great for those who can display it.<br /><br />But generally, i think subtler switching is the key, e.g. one, two or a few colours in a selected area and circumstance, like some edges or highlights. Changing hue is easier on the eye than changing brightness. In the latter case, if you can provide a material reason for the varyingly visible flicker (striplight or candle light), it's better.</div>

					
